#. </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a
#. class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc502"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts502"></a>
msgctxt "thag8.2:5.1"
msgid "“Akkodhanonupanāhī,"
msgstr "Without anger or resentment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:5.2"
msgid "amāyo rittapesuṇo;"
msgstr "Without deceit, and rid of slander,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:5.3"
msgid "Sa ve tādisako bhikkhu,"
msgstr "Such a monk, poised,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:5.4"
msgid "evaṃ pecca na socati."
msgstr "Doesn’t sorrow after death."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc503"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts503"></a>
msgctxt "thag8.2:6.1"
msgid "Akkodhanonupanāhī,"
msgstr "Without anger or resentment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:6.2"
msgid "amāyo rittapesuṇo;"
msgstr "Without deceit, and rid of slander,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:6.3"
msgid "Guttadvāro sadā bhikkhu,"
msgstr "A monk with sense doors guarded,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:6.4"
msgid "evaṃ pecca na socati."
msgstr "Doesn’t sorrow after death."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc504"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts504"></a>
msgctxt "thag8.2:7.1"
msgid "Akkodhanonupanāhī,"
msgstr "Without anger or resentment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:7.2"
msgid "amāyo rittapesuṇo;"
msgstr "Without deceit, and rid of slander,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:7.3"
msgid "Kalyāṇasīlo <span class=\"var\" title=\"yo (s2, s3, pts1)\" id=\"note253\">so</span> bhikkhu,"
msgstr "A monk of good virtue"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:7.4"
msgid "evaṃ pecca na socati."
msgstr "Doesn’t sorrow after death."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc505"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts505"></a>
msgctxt "thag8.2:8.1"
msgid "Akkodhanonupanāhī,"
msgstr "Without anger or resentment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:8.2"
msgid "amāyo rittapesuṇo;"
msgstr "Without deceit, and rid of slander,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:8.3"
msgid "Kalyāṇamitto <span class=\"var\" title=\"yo (s2, s3, pts1)\" id=\"note254\">so</span> bhikkhu,"
msgstr "A monk with good friends"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:8.4"
msgid "evaṃ pecca na socati."
msgstr "Doesn’t sorrow after death."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc506"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts506"></a><a class="pts" id="pts53"></a>
msgctxt "thag8.2:9.1"
msgid "Akkodhanonupanāhī,"
msgstr "Without anger or resentment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:9.2"
msgid "amāyo rittapesuṇo;"
msgstr "Without deceit, and rid of slander,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:9.3"
msgid "Kalyāṇapañño <span class=\"var\" title=\"yo (s2, s3, pts1)\" id=\"note255\">so</span> bhikkhu,"
msgstr "A monk of good wisdom,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:9.4"
msgid "evaṃ pecca na socati."
msgstr "Doesn’t sorrow after death."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
msgctxt "thag8.2:10.1"
msgid "<span class=\"cross\" title=\"^sn11.14#1 [14. Daliddasutta] | ^sn55.26#1 [26. Paṭhamaanāthapiṇḍikasutta] | ^an4.52#1 [52. Dutiyapuññābhisandasutta] | ^an5.47#1 [47. Dhanasutta] | ^tha-ap65#3 [Paccāgamaniyattheraapadāna] | ^pe3#56 [Suttādhiṭṭhānatatiyabhūmi]\" id=\"note256\">*</span> <a class=\"verse-num-sc\" id=\"verse-num-sc507\"></a><a class=\"verse-num-pts\" id=\"verse-num-pts507\"></a>Yassa saddhā tathāgate,"
msgstr "Whoever has faith in the Tathāgata,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:10.2"
msgid "acalā suppatiṭṭhitā;"
msgstr "That is unshakable and firmly established,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:10.3"
msgid "Sīlañca yassa kalyāṇaṃ,"
msgstr "Whose ethics are good,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:10.4"
msgid "ariyakantaṃ pasaṃsitaṃ."
msgstr "Pleasing to the noble ones, and praiseworthy,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc508"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts508"></a>
msgctxt "thag8.2:11.1"
msgid "Saṃghe pasādo yassatthi,"
msgstr "Who has confidence in the Saṅgha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:11.2"
msgid "ujubhūtañca dassanaṃ;"
msgstr "And whose vision is straight—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:11.3"
msgid "‘Adaliddo’ti taṃ āhu,"
msgstr "they’re said to be prosperous,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:11.4"
msgid "amoghaṃ tassa jīvitaṃ."
msgstr "Their life is not wasted."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc509"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts509"></a>
msgctxt "thag8.2:12.1"
msgid "Tasmā saddhañca sīlañca,"
msgstr "Therefore a wise person would devote themselves"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:12.2"
msgid "pasādaṃ dhammadassanaṃ;"
msgstr "To faith, virtue,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:12.3"
msgid "Anuyuñjetha medhāvī,"
msgstr "Confidence, and the vision of Dhamma,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag8.2:12.4"
msgid "saraṃ buddhāna sāsanan”ti."
msgstr "Remembering the teaching of the Buddhas."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
